最高法院于2020年10月7日听取了口头辩论。由于COVID-19持续流行，口头辩论通过电话会议进行。<ref name="cnbc oral"/> [[露丝·贝德尔·金斯伯格|露丝·贝德尔·金斯伯格]]法官在此前一个月去世，其继任者[[埃米·科尼·巴雷特|埃米·科尼·巴雷特]]法官的任命尚未被确认，因此巴雷特法官并未参与本案。<ref name="ap decision"/>依据对庭审的观察报道，法官在版权问题上似乎支持甲骨文，但他们也尊重微软支持谷歌的论点（微软的意见书辩称，倾向甲骨文的裁决可能会颠覆软件行业）。法官们的部分问题亦聚焦于版权法的思想—表达二分原则以及合并原则如何适用于API。[[尼尔·戈萨奇|尼尔·戈萨奇]]法官还重点关注了第七修正案的问题，以及联邦巡回区法院推翻陪审团裁决是否正确的问题。<ref name="cnbc oral">{{cite web | url = https://www.cnbc.com/2020/10/07/supreme-court-hears-google-v-oracle-software-copyright-case.html | title = Justices wary of upending tech industry in Google v. Oracle Supreme Court fight | first = Tucker | last = Higgens | date = October 7, 2020 | access-date = October 7, 2020 | work = [[CNBC|CNBC]] | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109141229/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/10/07/supreme-court-hears-google-v-oracle-software-copyright-case.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.ipwatchdog.com/2020/10/07/justices-look-reassurance-sky-wont-fall-google-v-oracle/id=126052/ | title = Justices Look for Reassurance That the Sky Won't Fall When They Rule in Google v. Oracle | first = Eileen | last = McDermott | date = October 7, 2020 | access-date = October 8, 2020 | work = IP Watchdog | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109141448/https://www.ipwatchdog.com/2020/10/07/justices-look-reassurance-sky-wont-fall-google-v-oracle/id=126052/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

===判决===
最高法院于2021年4月5日，以6票对2票的多数判决谷歌对Java API的使用属于合理使用，推翻了联邦巡回区上诉法院的判决，并将案件发回进一步审理。[[斯蒂芬·布雷耶|斯蒂芬·布雷耶]]法官撰写了法庭多数意见。

判决认可了上诉法院关于合理使用审查的意见，认为合理使用兼具事实问题和法律问题两面性，陪审团仅认定事实问题，但能否根据事实得出合理使用的结论仍然由法官决定。也因此，上诉法院推翻陪审团裁决的行为与宪法第七修正案“由陪审团裁决的事实……不得重新审查”的规定并不冲突，谷歌要求由陪审团对合理使用作最终决定的主张没有法律依据。

布雷耶假定API受到版权保护，进而直接对衡量合理使用的四个因素进行了审查：<ref name="cnn decision"/><ref name="scotusblog decision">{{cite web | url = https://www.scotusblog.com/2021/04/justices-validate-googles-use-of-java-platform-in-android-software-code/|title = Justices validate Google's use of Java platform in Android software code|first=Ronald|last=Mann|date=April 6, 2021|accessdate=April 7, 2021|work={{le|SCOTUSBlog}}|archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109141225/https://www.scotusblog.com/2021/04/justices-validate-googles-use-of-java-platform-in-android-software-code/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

# 受版权保护作品的性质：布雷耶认为，API仅作为声明代码而非具体的实现，在版权法的语境下，它发挥类似于[[杜威十进制图书分类法|杜威十进制图书分类法]]的“组织功能”，这一性质导致合理使用更易适用。.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://lawandcrime.com/supreme-court/the-supreme-court-just-sided-with-google-for-copying-lines-of-code-justice-thomas-went-off/ | title = The Supreme Court Just Sided with Google's Copying of Thousands of Lines of Code. Justice Thomas Went Off. | first = Elura | last = Nanos | date = April 5, 2021 | accessdate = April 5, 2021 | work = {{le|Law and Crime}} | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109140938/https://lawandcrime.com/supreme-court/the-supreme-court-just-sided-with-google-for-copying-lines-of-code-justice-thomas-went-off/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>
# 使用的目的和性质：布雷耶表示，谷歌使用并改造Java API的行为“目的在于扩展基于安卓系统的智能手机的功能和实用性”，而这“创造了一个能让程序员轻松使用的新平台”。<ref name="scotusblog decision"/>他还写道，谷歌对Java API的使用“仅以实现智能手机程序的实用性所需为限”。<ref name="scotusblog decision"/>
# 被复制受保护内容的数量和实质性：布雷耶认为，谷歌只使用了大约0.4%的 Java源代码，可忽略不计。针对实质性的问题，他写道，谷歌没有复制Java实现功能所需的核心代码：“谷歌复制这些代码，不是因为它们多么有创造力或多么美观，甚至（某种程度上）也不是因为它们自身的目的。谷歌复制这些代码只是因为程序员已经习惯了使用Java SE，如果没有它们，将很难……吸引程序员使用……安卓系统。”<ref name="scotusblog decision"/>
# 复制行为的市场效应：布雷耶认为，谷歌在复制Java API时，尚不清楚安卓系统是否会成功，安卓系统不应被视为 Java 的替代品，而应为在不同平台上运行的产品。<ref name="scotusblog decision"/>布雷耶进一步表示，如果判决支持甲骨文，“可能会对公众造成威胁”，因为“只有甲骨文将掌握关键内容。这一结果很可能为甲骨文（或其他拥有计算机接口版权的公司）带来极高的利益。……（但是）这种控制力与作为版权法基础的激励创造的目标相冲突，而不是进一步助益该目标。”<ref name="cnn decision"/>

布雷耶就此认定，谷歌对API的使用满足所有四个因素的要求，谷歌的使用“只是允许用户将他们积累的才能用于新的转换性的平台所必需的”。<ref name="cnn decision">{{cite web | url = https://www.cnn.com/2021/04/05/tech/google-oracle-supreme-court-ruling/index.html | title = Supreme Court hands Google a victory in a multibillion-dollar case against Oracle | first = Brian | last = Fung | date = April 5, 2021 | accessdate = April 5, 2021 | publisher = [[CNN|CNN]] | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109140933/https://www.cnn.com/2021/04/05/tech/google-oracle-supreme-court-ruling/index.html | dead-url = no }}</ref> 既然谷歌的复制行为构成合理使用，没有违反版权法，<ref name="ap decision">{{cite web | url = https://abcnews.go.com/Business/wireStory/top-court-sides-google-copyright-dispute-oracle-76878874 | title = Top court sides with Google in copyright dispute with Oracle | first = Jessica | last = Gresko | date = April 5, 2021 | accessdate = April 5, 2021 | publisher = [[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] | via = [[ABC_News|ABC News]] | archive-date = 2022-01-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220111093314/https://abcnews.go.com/Business/wireStory/top-court-sides-google-copyright-dispute-oracle-76878874 | dead-url = no }}</ref>那么认定API是否受版权保护亦不再必要。

[[克拉伦斯·托马斯|克拉伦斯·托马斯]]大法官撰写了一份反对意见，[[塞缪尔·阿利托|塞缪尔·阿利托]]大法官亦联名支持该意见。<ref name="cnbc decision">{{cite web | url = https://www.cnbc.com/2021/04/05/supreme-court-rules-in-googles-favor-in-copyright-dispute-with-oracle-over-android-software.html | title = Supreme Court rules in Google's favor in copyright dispute with Oracle over Android software | first = Tucker | last = Higgens | date = April 5, 2021 | accessdate = April 5, 2021 | publisher = [[CNBC|CNBC]] | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109140935/https://www.cnbc.com/2021/04/05/supreme-court-rules-in-googles-favor-in-copyright-dispute-with-oracle-over-android-software.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>托马斯写道，多数意见在实施代码和声明代码之间划分了一种国会立法者未曾允许的区别，进而，“这种扭曲的分析导致了以下结果：很难想象声明代码还能在什么情况下受到版权保护。”<ref name="verge decision">{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/5/22367851/google-oracle-supreme-court-ruling-java-android-api | title = Supreme Court sides with Google in Oracle's API copyright case | first1 = Russell | last1 = Brandom | first2 = Aid | last2 = Robertson | date = April 5, 2021 | accessdate = April 5, 2021 | work = [[The_Verge|The Verge]] | archive-date = 2022-01-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220112180049/https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/5/22367851/google-oracle-supreme-court-ruling-java-android-api | dead-url = no }}</ref> 他进一步表示，在他自己的合理使用分析下，“谷歌对受版权保护代码的使用绝非合理。”<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2021/04/05/supreme-court-googles-use-oracle-code-android-fair-use/4339371001/ | title = Supreme Court sides with Google in years long fight with tech giant Oracle | first = John | last = Fritze | date = April 5, 2021 | accessdate = April 5, 2021 | work = [[USA_Today|USA Today]] | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109061805/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2021/04/05/supreme-court-googles-use-oracle-code-android-fair-use/4339371001/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

==影响==
谷歌与甲骨文的诉讼为科技行业密切关注。鉴于 API 的大量使用，如果司法判决有利于甲骨文，可能对过去和未来的软件开发都产生重大影响。<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/oracle-wins-court-ruling-against-google-in-long-running-copyright-case-1522164091 | title = Oracle Wins Court Ruling Against Google in Multibillion-Dollar Copyright Case | first1 = Brent | last1 = Kendall | first2 = Jay | last2 = Greene | date = March 27, 2018 | access-date = March 27, 2018 | work = [[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]] | archive-date = 2022-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220109141230/https://www.wsj.com/articles/oracle-wins-court-ruling-against-google-in-long-running-copyright-case-1522164091 | dead-url = no }}</ref>包括谷歌及其他基于安卓系统的开发人员在内，反对上诉法院判决的人或是从互操作性、对软件创新的影响等各方面提出了他们的担忧，或是指出，既有接口的版权人可能以其权利恶意挟持那些善意信赖相应标准开放性的下游开发者。如果API受到版权保护，下游企业将不得不故意采用不兼容的标准以免面临复杂的诉讼风险。而这与当前的行业趋势——​​提高不同服务之间的互操作性，允许程序之间的交流，为终端用户建设更加一体化的平台——是不相容的。<ref name=atechnica>{{cite web | url = https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2019/01/google-asks-supreme-court-to-overrule-disastrous-ruling-on-api-copyrights/ | title = Google asks Supreme Court to overrule disastrous ruling on API copyrights | first = Timothy | last = Lee | date = January 25, 2019 | access-date = January 25, 2019 | work = [[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]] | archive-date = 2019-04-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190423084450/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2019/01/google-asks-supreme-court-to-overrule-disastrous-ruling-on-api-copyrights/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="arstech openjdk">{{cite web | url = https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/01/android-n-switches-to-openjdk-google-tells-oracle-it-is-protected-by-the-gpl/ | title = Android N switches to OpenJDK, Google tells Oracle it is protected by the GPL | first = Ron | last = Amadeo | date = January 6, 2016 | access-date = March 30, 2018 | work = [[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]] | archive-date = 2017-03-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170312065019/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/01/android-n-switches-to-openjdk-google-tells-oracle-it-is-protected-by-the-gpl/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

[[连线|《连线》杂志]]以[[Linux|Linux]]操作系统为例：Linux是完全开源的，但它所采用的[[可移植操作系统接口|POSIX]]是一套模仿[[Unix|Unix]]操作系统以实现高度互操作性的API。编程人员只需要编写一组代码，就可以在具有相同API的任何系统上编译，即使系统的计算架构不同。如果甲骨文胜诉，则Unix的当前所有者[[Micro_Focus|Micro Focus]]公司可能会向所有试图将基于POSIX的操作系统的开发者寻求赔偿。<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.wired.com/2016/05/oracle-google-case-will-decide-future-software/ | title = The Oracle-Google Case Will Decide The Future Of Software | first = Klint | last = Finley | date = May 23, 2016 | accessdate = March 27, 2018 | work = [[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]] | archive-date = 2021-11-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211101051622/https://www.wired.com/2016/05/oracle-google-case-will-decide-future-software/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

